OL,3,CThe Somerset farmers fighting for a
OL,4,CBritish wool revival
OL,6,FThe British Wool Marketing Board
OL,7,Frepresents farmers in the
OL,8,Finternational textiles industry.
OL,10,FAndrew Hogley, CEO for the board, said
OL,11,Fdespite many farmers feeling at a loss
OL,12,Fwith the situation, things are
OL,13,Fstarting to change.
OL,15,FHe said: "I think we're starting to
OL,16,Fsee a shift. A lot of the key brands
OL,17,Fand manufacturers and sustainability
OL,18,Fpeople, are now starting to influence
OL,19,Fthe purchasing decisions, the sourcing
OL,20,Fdecisions of those organisations.
